business_analysis.business_domain: Local peer-to-peer marketplace platform enabling individuals to buy and sell used and new items within their communities
business_analysis.business_model: Commission-based marketplace with revenue from listing promotions, featured placements, shipping services, and potentially transaction fees on facilitated sales
key_products_services: Mobile and web marketplace platform for local buying/selling
Item listing and discovery service across 15+ categories
Seller promotion and featured listing services
business_analysis.target_customers: Individual consumers looking to buy or sell secondhand goods, vehicles, collectibles, and various merchandise locally; includes casual sellers, frequent resellers, small businesses, and bargain hunters

key_entities.name: users
key_entities.description: Individual buyers and sellers on the platform, with dual roles

key_entities.name: listings
key_entities.description: Items posted for sale across 15+ categories including vehicles, electronics, home goods, clothing, collectibles

key_entities.name: transactions
key_entities.description: Completed sales between buyers and sellers

key_entities.name: categories
key_entities.description: Product taxonomy including Electronics, Vehicles, Home & Garden, Clothing, Baby & Kids, Collectibles, etc.

key_entities.name: messages
key_entities.description: In-app communications between buyers and sellers for negotiation

key_entities.name: locations
key_entities.description: Geographic data for local transactions (city, state, zip code)

key_entities.name: searches
key_entities.description: User search queries and browse behavior

key_entities.name: promotions
key_entities.description: Paid listing enhancements and featured placements

data_products.name: Seller Analytics Dashboard
data_products.description: Likely provides sellers with listing performance metrics, views, messages received, and sales data

data_products.name: Search and Discovery API
data_products.description: Powers listing search, filtering, and recommendation features across web and mobile

data_products.name: Trust & Safety Scoring
data_products.description: Fraud detection and user reputation scoring system

primary_use_cases: Marketplace health monitoring and GMV tracking
Fraud detection and trust & safety monitoring
Listing quality and completion rate analysis
Revenue optimization from promotions and services
business_questions: What is the conversion rate from listing view to message to completed sale?
Which categories have the highest GMV and fastest time-to-sale?
What are the pricing trends for popular items like vehicles and electronics?
Which geographic markets show the strongest buyer and seller activity?
What is the cohort retention of new users over 90 days?
How effective are promoted listings at driving sales?
What percentage of listings result in successful transactions?
What are the peak listing and buying times by day/week/season?
Which user segments are most valuable (power sellers vs casual users)?
What is the correlation between response time and sale completion?
How does listing quality (photos, description) impact sale probability?
What are the fraud patterns and high-risk transaction indicators?
What is the customer lifetime value by acquisition channel?
How do local market dynamics differ across cities and states?
demo_opportunities: Build a marketplace health dashboard showing GMV, active listings, and transaction trends
Create category performance analysis comparing vehicles, electronics, and home goods
Demonstrate geographic heat mapping of buyer/seller activity by state and city
Show cohort analysis of user retention and lifetime value
Build conversion funnel from search to view to message to sale
Create pricing analytics showing market trends and competitive positioning
Demonstrate fraud detection patterns using transaction and user behavior data
Show seller performance scorecards with listing quality and response metrics
Build search effectiveness analysis with query-to-conversion tracking
Create seasonal demand forecasting for key categories
Demonstrate A/B test analysis for promoted listing effectiveness
Show real-time inventory monitoring by category and location

additional_context.geographic_focus: US (with evidence of nationwide coverage across multiple states including NE, IA, IL, FL, TX, CA)
notable_features: Strong local/geographic focus with city-level targeting
Diverse category mix from low-value items ($10-20) to high-value vehicles ($40K+)
Mobile-first platform with app download emphasis
Trust and safety critical to business model
Dual-sided marketplace dynamics requiring balance of supply and demand
Competes with Facebook Marketplace, Craigslist, Mercari, and Poshmark
Heavy vehicle inventory suggests dealer partnerships or power sellers
Price range from $7 to $69,950 indicates broad market coverage
